# dora-openarm-camera

A [dora-rs](https://dora-rs.ai/) node that captures **RGB frames from real cameras**:
Intel RealSense D435i and Orbbec Gemini 335Lg, over V4L2 (UVC YUYV color stream).
Only the color stream is used — depth (Z16) / infrared (Y8I) / metadata nodes are skipped.

This replaces `dora-openarm-dummy-camera` (which emits random images) for real data collection.

## Camera identification

The `/dev/videoN` number is volatile and some RealSense units ship without a USB
serial, so each camera is identified by its **USB port path** (stable as long as the
camera stays plugged into the same USB port). The node scans `v4l2-ctl` output for the
color (YUYV) node whose `Bus info` matches `DEVICE_PATH`.

Current mapping on this device:

| Role (dataflow node)   | Camera            | DEVICE_PATH                | Resolution |
| ---------------------- | ----------------- | -------------------------- | ---------- |
| `camera-ceiling` (top) | Orbbec 335Lg      | `usb-xhci-hcd.16.auto-1`   | 640x480    |
| `camera-wrist-left`    | RealSense D435i   | `usb-xhci-hcd.10.auto-1.2` | 1280x720   |
| `camera-wrist-right`   | RealSense D435i   | `usb-xhci-hcd.10.auto-1.1` | 1280x720   |

## Configuration (env / args)

| Env             | Default   | Meaning                                                              |
| --------------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `DEVICE_PATH`   | —         | USB port path used to find the color node (see table above).         |
| `CAMERA_TYPE`   | realsense | `realsense` or `orbbec`. RealSense applies a fixed WB color temp.    |
| `IMAGE_WIDTH`   | 1280      | Output image width.                                                  |
| `IMAGE_HEIGHT`  | 720       | Output image height.                                                 |
| `ENCODING`      | jpeg      | `jpeg` / `rgb8` / `yuv420` / `png` / `webp` / `bmp`.                 |
| `JPEG_QUALITY`  | 90        | JPEG quality (0-100).                                                |
| `WB_KELVIN`     | 5400      | RealSense manual white-balance color temperature (offsets cool tint).|
| `TARGET_BGR`    | —         | Optional `B,G,R` for per-channel gain alignment (see note).          |

## Color note

RealSense D435i is a depth camera; its UVC color stream auto white-balance runs cool
(greenish-blue). This node uses auto exposure (consistent with Orbbec) plus a fixed WB
color temperature to get a natural baseline.

The three cameras run as **independent dora nodes in parallel**, so — unlike the
standalone `grab_rgb.py` — they cannot share a live Orbbec frame as a white-balance
reference. If you need the RealSense channels to track a target, set `TARGET_BGR` to a
fixed `B,G,R` (e.g. the Orbbec baseline ~`108,108,105`); per-channel gain then pulls the
RealSense means toward that target. This is a static approximation, not a per-frame lock.

